com.tomtom.speedtools.apivalidation

Class ApiValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tomtom.speedtools.apivalidation.ApiValidator

  • public final class ApiValidator
extends Object
    The class WebParameterValidator implements a simple way to validate monitoring parameters and throw a BAD_REQUEST (HTTP status code 400) is a parameter is not ok.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Reset the validator. This should only be used if you must use a setter on an object after the validation has run, e.g. to modify your DTO element after reading it. You should manually called validate() after setting the attributes.

      • checkDouble

        public void checkDouble(boolean required,
                        @Nonnull
                        String name,
                        @Nullable
                        Double value,
                        double min,
                        double max,
                        boolean positiveInfinityAllowed)
        Check a double value.
        Parameters:
        required - Specifies whether value may be null or not.
        name - Name of value.
        value - Actual value.
        min - Minimum value.
        max - Maximum value.
        positiveInfinityAllowed - The value of positiveInfinityAllowed indicates whether or not Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY is allowed as a value or not. If positiveInfinityAllowed is false, the value must be in range [min, max] (inclusive). If positiveInfinityAllowed is true, the value must either be in range [min, max] or may be Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY. Note that Double.NEGATIVE_INFINITY is never allowed.
